article.headline: W. Kentucky 95, Towson 72
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ky. (AP) -- Courtney Lee scored 21 points and Orlando Mendez-Valdez came off the bench to add a career-high 15 as Western Kentucky rolled to a 95-72 victory over Towson on Tuesday night. Lee scored 15 of his 21 points in the second half for the Hilltoppers (4-0). The junior made 9 of 16 shots from the floor, including 3 of 6 3-point attempts. Mendez-Valdez also added a team-high seven assists for the Hilltoppers. Towson (2-2), which trailed 43-28 at halftime, steadily fell farther behind Western Kentucky in the second half, despite shooting 68 percent from the floor (15 of 22) after halftime. The Hilltoppers enjoyed their biggest lead of 25 points with 1:12 to play before emptying the bench in the final minutes. Tommmy Breaux paced four Tigers in double figures with 14 points. Gary Neal added 13, while Rocky Coleman and Winstonn Tubbs scored 10 points each. The Hilltoppers made 33 of 61 shots (54 percent) in the game and hit 11 of 27 3-point tries (41 percent).
